                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15069843" author="okram" created="Wed, 23 Dec 2015 16:37:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is because of the limitations of &lt;tt&gt;LambdaStep&lt;/tt&gt;. I&apos;ve been batting around the idea of adding a &lt;tt&gt;boolean&lt;/tt&gt; method for runtime determination of whether its a &quot;true lambda&quot; or not. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15095040" author="okram" created="Tue, 12 Jan 2016 21:52:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This has to do with how Groovy determines the function to call on the class. &lt;tt&gt;T&lt;/tt&gt; is seen as a &lt;tt&gt;Function&lt;/tt&gt;. This is bad. I had this same problem with &lt;tt&gt;Column&lt;/tt&gt;. Thus, I tweaked the &lt;tt&gt;GraphTraversal.by(Function)&lt;/tt&gt; method accordingly and now things behave as expected.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;gremlin&amp;gt; g = TinkerFactory.createModern().traversal(GraphTraversalSource.build().with(LambdaRestrictionStrategy.instance()))
==&amp;gt;graphtraversalsource[tinkergraph[vertices:6 edges:6], standard]
gremlin&amp;gt; g.V().groupCount().by{it.get().label()}
The provided traversal contains a lambda step: LambdaMapStep(lambda)
Display stack trace? [yN]
gremlin&amp;gt; g.V().groupCount().by(label)
==&amp;gt;[software:2, person:4]
gremlin&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
